SSRF--> SSRF Vulnerability occur when application is fetching resources remote resources without validating user supply.Types 2 :- 1)Regular/Inband 2)Blind/Outof bind

-->identify any request parameters that contains hostnames, IP address or full URLS
--> decimal-encoded version of 127.0.0.1 is 2130706433
--> 127.1 resolves to 127.0.0.1
--> Octal representation of 127.0.0.1 is 017700000001

--> DNS Rebinding--> register a domain that resolves to internal IP address
--> HTTP Redirection --> use your own server that redirects to an internal IP address
